Legal regulations of project-based accounting and reporting. Underlying principles and concepts of project-based accounting. Distinctive features of project-based accounting for a business. Basic schemes of accounting in terms of types of accounting. Costs, benefits, transactions and income statement. Reporting. The essence and schemes of project finance. Funding, budget, profitability calculation and risk analysis of a business plan. Project funding with the EU grants from different funds. Various project funding application forms and requirements.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to improve the learner's knowledge of the
essential terminology, formula, and methodology of Project-Based Finance, and practice using them in writing the EU funding applications and an investment project.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) can use legal regulations of project-based accounting; 2) can use project-based accounting and reporting; 3) knows the specificity of project finance; 4) can compose the EU funding applications; 5) can evaluate the cost-effectiveness and risk of investment projects.
